cs.CR, cs.AR, cs.SE, cs.ET, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper discusses fault injection attacks on cryptographic and secured algorithms implementations, which falls under the scope of cs.CR.
2. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) - The paper focuses on the ARMv7-M architecture and describes a practical EMFI platform, which falls under the scope of cs.AR.
3. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper discusses vulnerabilities in software of secured embedded systems and proposes a methodology for fault injections, which falls under the scope of cs.SE.
4. cs.ET (Embedded Systems) - The paper discusses fault injection attacks on embedded systems and proposes a methodology for fault injections, which falls under the scope of cs.ET.
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the effects of fault injections on the control flow and how it can be used to mount powerful attacks, which falls under the scope of cs.SY.
